<div id="banner">
	<h1>Software that Sucks</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p>&#8220;How sad to see two leading Democrats fall for, even feed the lie that they can create user-oriented software for free.&#8221;</p>

<p>- <a href="http://archive.scripting.com/2003/12/24#editorial">Dave Winer, Scripting News, 12/24/2003</a></p>

<p>We have recently learned that the following software is not oriented to users. All users should stop using these products immediately.</p>

<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.mailtothefuture.com/">Mail to the Future</a> (spare time)</li>
<li><a href="http://www.friendster.com/">Friendster</a> (ads)</li>
<li><a href="http://ranchero.com/netnewswire/#lite">NetNewsWire Lite</a> (trial version)</li>
<li><a href="http://www.apple.com/itunes/">iTunes</a> (bundled)</li>
<li><a href="http://www.codingmonkeys.de/subethaedit/">SubEthaEdit</a> (volunteers)</li>
<li><a href="http://creativecommons.org/">Creative Commons</a> (grant)</li>
<li><a href="http://www.opensecrets.org/">OpenSecrets</a> (donations)</li>
</ul>

<p>Once again, the only way user-oriented software can be made is if users purchase it. Anything else is physically impossible.</p>

<p class="posted">posted December 24, 2003 01:08 PM (<a class="category" href="http://www.aaronsw.com/weblog/cat_others">Others</a>)  <a href="001101" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
</div>

